1
00:00:30,781 --> 00:00:32,088
Kazumi.

2
00:00:35,723 --> 00:00:37,323
You're awake?

3
00:00:39,371 --> 00:00:40,731
Feeling okay?

4
00:00:42,043 --> 00:00:45,796
Yeah, much better now.

5
00:00:46,720 --> 00:00:48,801
Sorry, it's your day off.

6
00:00:48,801 --> 00:00:50,728
It's fine.

7
00:00:50,728 --> 00:00:53,071
I made porridge. Want some?

8
00:00:53,071 --> 00:00:54,071
Yeah.

9
00:00:58,813 --> 00:01:03,952
Darn, the weather's perfect
for a date though.

10
00:01:07,984 --> 00:01:11,736
Once you're better,
we'll go wherever you want, Himari.

11
00:01:11,736 --> 00:01:12,816
Okay.

12
00:01:15,219 --> 00:01:16,842
Thanks.

13
00:01:16,842 --> 00:01:18,462
Time to eat.

14
00:01:18,462 --> 00:01:20,343
Oh, wait.

15
00:01:21,182 --> 00:01:22,542
It's hot.

16
00:01:29,880 --> 00:01:32,599
I can eat by myself.

17
00:01:32,599 --> 00:01:37,004
Come on, just let yourself
be spoiled at times like this.

18
00:01:37,004 --> 00:01:39,117
Come on, open wide.

19
00:01:47,469 --> 00:01:48,782
Is it good?

20
00:01:49,618 --> 00:01:50,911
Yeah.

21
00:01:52,459 --> 00:01:54,194
Good.

22
00:01:54,194 --> 00:01:55,851
Want some fruit too?

23
00:01:55,851 --> 00:01:57,110
Yeah.

24
00:01:57,110 --> 00:01:58,738
Be right back.

25
00:02:04,795 --> 00:02:08,497
- I didn't have a mom around, remember?
- Yeah.

26
00:02:08,497 --> 00:02:15,477
So when I had a fever as a kid,
my dad fed me porridge like this.

27
00:02:15,477 --> 00:02:17,690
I'd get so happy.

28
00:02:19,837 --> 00:02:24,239
You know, Kazumi,
I think you'd make a great father.

29
00:02:25,101 --> 00:02:27,511
- You think so?
- Yeah.

30
00:02:28,996 --> 00:02:33,758
Your parents must be wonderful people too.

31
00:02:33,758 --> 00:02:38,053
After all, they say children take after
their parents.

32
00:02:44,144 --> 00:02:46,004
Are you okay?

33
00:02:46,004 --> 00:02:49,012
Oh, sorry, my hand slipped.

34
00:02:50,334 --> 00:02:51,941
Be careful.

35
00:04:10,970 --> 00:04:14,424
<i>I didn't have a mom around, remember?</i>

36
00:04:14,424 --> 00:04:21,745
When I had a fever as a kid,
my dad fed me porridge like this.

37
00:04:23,035 --> 00:04:25,348
Family memories, huh?

38
00:04:27,005 --> 00:04:30,213
<i>As for my family... It was falling apart.</i>

39
00:04:30,213 --> 00:04:33,211
- You're going to that woman, huh?
- Shut up!

40
00:04:33,211 --> 00:04:35,471
Who do you think pays the bills?

41
00:04:35,471 --> 00:04:37,184
<i>My father had an affair.</i>

42
00:04:37,890 --> 00:04:41,843
<i>My mother blamed my father,
and he just doubled down.</i>

43
00:04:45,286 --> 00:04:49,316
<i>From that day on, there was no peace at home.</i>

44
00:04:50,755 --> 00:04:55,927
<i>All I could do
was protect my younger brother, Koki.</i>

45
00:05:04,412 --> 00:05:07,366
<i>After my father's affair came to light,</i>

46
00:05:07,366 --> 00:05:10,655
<i>my mother became emotionally unstable.</i>

47
00:05:13,395 --> 00:05:18,203
<i>I mediated between them
to keep fights from breaking out.</i>

48
00:05:21,968 --> 00:05:25,408
You won't betray me, will you, Kazumi?

49
00:05:28,338 --> 00:05:32,244
<i>That was my role in this family.</i>

50
00:05:42,207 --> 00:05:46,450
<i>But no matter how careful I was,</i>

51
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:52,015
<i>I'd stumble in unexpected ways.</i>

52
00:05:53,878 --> 00:05:56,353
Are all men like this?

53
00:05:56,353 --> 00:05:59,587
<i>My mother,
who was hostile to anything sexual,</i>

54
00:05:59,587 --> 00:06:04,591
<i>lectured me about how vulgar
and dirty such things were.</i>

55
00:06:04,591 --> 00:06:07,407
<i>And yet the urges still welled up.</i>

56
00:06:08,901 --> 00:06:11,261
It's for your own good, Kazumi.

57
00:06:11,261 --> 00:06:13,633
You understand, don't you?

58
00:06:16,078 --> 00:06:17,571
Yeah.

59
00:06:20,246 --> 00:06:24,654
You really are such a good,
understanding boy.

60
00:06:24,654 --> 00:06:27,351
<i>I'd smile without thinking.</i>

61
00:06:27,351 --> 00:06:30,932
Compared to you, Koki's just...

62
00:06:30,932 --> 00:06:33,078
Koki... Koki!

63
00:06:33,078 --> 00:06:35,550
Are you running away again?

64
00:06:35,550 --> 00:06:37,994
- Mom's worried about you!
- Get off me!

65
00:06:39,178 --> 00:06:42,587
Stop pretending to be a good brother.
It's gross.

66
00:06:47,577 --> 00:06:51,596
<i>That naive thought
that I was doing it for my brother...</i>

67
00:06:53,534 --> 00:06:56,893
<i>Everything was terrible.</i>

68
00:07:02,448 --> 00:07:07,132
<i>I ended up hurting everything
that matters to me.</i>

69
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:18,857
Apple bunnies...

70
00:07:26,055 --> 00:07:31,332
<i>But after meeting you, everything changed.</i>

71
00:07:35,293 --> 00:07:38,010
<i>For the first time,
I was able to love someone.</i>

72
00:07:39,127 --> 00:07:44,046
<i>I want to stay by that gentle smile forever.</i>

73
00:07:54,875 --> 00:07:58,750
<i>I shouldn't touch you
with these filthy hands.</i>

74
00:07:59,792 --> 00:08:05,111
<i>If I did, I'd make that smile vanish.</i>

75
00:08:16,093 --> 00:08:20,747
<i>But if someday,
someone else is going to pluck you,</i>

76
00:08:21,712 --> 00:08:26,352
<i>I want you to bloom by my side.</i>

77
00:08:27,511 --> 00:08:29,305
That's how I feel now.

78
00:08:30,577 --> 00:08:33,800
<i>You haven't told her much
about yourself, huh?</i>

79
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:36,747
If it were me, I'd tell her everything.

80
00:08:45,961 --> 00:08:48,561
<i>I can't leave Himari alone.</i>

81
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:51,453
[Vextos]

82
00:08:51,453 --> 00:08:56,043
Can I get your answer
on the Fukuoka business trip soon?

83
00:08:56,043 --> 00:08:59,671
I'm sorry. I'm still undecided.

84
00:08:59,671 --> 00:09:03,187
They're asking for you specifically.

85
00:09:03,187 --> 00:09:05,985
And if you pull this off,

86
00:09:05,985 --> 00:09:08,574
I can push for your promotion too.

87
00:09:08,574 --> 00:09:10,808
What is there to hesitate about?

88
00:09:11,796 --> 00:09:16,840
I'd rather see through
the current project with Yanami.

89
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:19,954
We'll have Shibasaki take that over.

90
00:09:19,954 --> 00:09:22,070
Nihei will support her.

91
00:09:22,070 --> 00:09:25,434
He's only in his second year,
but he's very capable.

92
00:09:26,091 --> 00:09:28,192
He is capable, but...

93
00:09:28,830 --> 00:09:31,732
Yanami is quite a difficult client...

94
00:09:31,732 --> 00:09:34,489
Trust and delegate to your colleagues.

95
00:09:34,489 --> 00:09:37,533
That's necessary for a leader.

96
00:09:37,533 --> 00:09:41,520
I want to entrust you
with the Fukuoka project.

97
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:44,700
You'll live up to my trust, won't you?

98
00:10:12,690 --> 00:10:15,157
You really do eat with such joy.

99
00:10:16,270 --> 00:10:19,116
I'm fully recovered now, thanks to you.

100
00:10:19,116 --> 00:10:22,039
Don't overeat and get a stomachache.

101
00:10:22,039 --> 00:10:25,294
Then I'll have you take care of me again.

102
00:10:25,294 --> 00:10:26,994
Oh, right.

103
00:10:26,994 --> 00:10:30,160
There's a place
I want to take you to, Kazumi.

104
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:32,050
Oh? Where?

105
00:10:32,050 --> 00:10:34,730
It's called Hamagasaki Beach.

106
00:10:34,730 --> 00:10:36,604
I went there once and it was amazing.

107
00:10:36,604 --> 00:10:39,017
I've been wanting to go there with you.

108
00:10:39,017 --> 00:10:40,532
How about next Sunday?

109
00:10:40,532 --> 00:10:41,946
Wanna go?

110
00:10:43,815 --> 00:10:45,750
Sunday, huh?

111
00:10:47,736 --> 00:10:49,844
Do you have plans?

112
00:10:51,817 --> 00:10:58,216
Sorry, I actually got a sudden request
to go on a Fukuoka business trip.

113
00:10:58,216 --> 00:11:02,190
My manager practically begged me,
and I couldn't say no.

114
00:11:02,190 --> 00:11:04,203
Oh, a business trip?

115
00:11:04,203 --> 00:11:06,227
When is it?

116
00:11:06,227 --> 00:11:08,537
This weekend, for two weeks.

117
00:11:09,481 --> 00:11:12,729
My manager said
it might even lead to a promotion.

118
00:11:13,851 --> 00:11:18,926
But I was worried
you'd feel lonely while I'm gone.

119
00:11:21,971 --> 00:11:24,846
That's amazing! It's a great opportunity!

120
00:11:25,556 --> 00:11:27,670
I'll be fine.

121
00:11:27,670 --> 00:11:31,635
Don't worry about me. Go give it your all!

122
00:11:34,645 --> 00:11:36,552
I see.

123
00:11:39,239 --> 00:11:43,051
Then let's go to Hamagasaki Beach
when I get back.

124
00:11:43,051 --> 00:11:45,482
Okay, I'm looking forward to it.

125
00:11:47,294 --> 00:11:48,731
All right then.

126
00:11:50,048 --> 00:11:53,754
You'll be taking over my project, Himari.

127
00:11:53,754 --> 00:11:57,669
Nihei will be supporting you,
so do your best together.

128
00:11:58,460 --> 00:12:02,305
And have Ando and the others
help with the materials.

129
00:12:02,305 --> 00:12:05,289
Got it. We'll all do our best.

130
00:12:05,289 --> 00:12:06,982
Thank you.

131
00:12:06,982 --> 00:12:10,265
Okay, let's finish eating
and I'll hand the work over to you.

132
00:12:10,265 --> 00:12:12,532
Okay! Let's eat.

133
00:12:22,048 --> 00:12:24,936
<i>Well, I guess that's just how it is.</i>

134
00:12:26,029 --> 00:12:28,013
<i>I wonder why...</i>

135
00:12:28,013 --> 00:12:31,707
<i>Sometimes I feel like Himari's so far away.</i>

136
00:12:33,109 --> 00:12:35,142
<i>Two weeks, huh?</i>

137
00:12:35,895 --> 00:12:40,057
<i>It'll fly by, but still... I'll miss him.</i>

138
00:12:42,939 --> 00:12:47,571
They're quick to respond over there,
so try to reply within the same day.

139
00:12:47,571 --> 00:12:53,861
<i>But this is a big chance.
I want Kazumi to do his best.</i>

140
00:12:53,861 --> 00:12:57,198
<i>He's supported me so much.</i>

141
00:12:57,198 --> 00:13:00,363
<i>I'll do my best too, and support him!</i>

142
00:13:00,363 --> 00:13:01,983
- Thank you.
- Sure.

143
00:13:07,598 --> 00:13:09,158
All right.

144
00:13:11,249 --> 00:13:13,773
Man, what's going on with this?

145
00:13:15,691 --> 00:13:17,536
What's wrong?

146
00:13:17,536 --> 00:13:21,953
Well, it's jammed, but I can't tell where.

147
00:13:22,610 --> 00:13:25,024
I'm good at this. Let me try.

148
00:13:28,748 --> 00:13:30,722
I think it's here.

149
00:13:33,354 --> 00:13:35,568
Oh, I found it.

150
00:13:35,568 --> 00:13:37,912
I can't reach it.

151
00:13:37,912 --> 00:13:39,503
Let's see here.

152
00:13:40,365 --> 00:13:42,080
Let's see...

153
00:13:42,797 --> 00:13:44,370
What's up?

154
00:13:46,966 --> 00:13:51,319
Something got stuck in the back.

155
00:13:51,319 --> 00:13:54,206
Here, try using this.

156
00:13:54,206 --> 00:13:56,513
You sure? Thanks.

157
00:14:02,657 --> 00:14:04,264
I got it!

158
00:14:05,239 --> 00:14:06,802
Good work.

159
00:14:06,802 --> 00:14:08,636
You really helped me.

160
00:14:08,636 --> 00:14:10,599
- It's nothing.
- I'll do the rest.

161
00:14:10,599 --> 00:14:13,363
- Oh, got it. I'll toss this out.
- Thanks.

162
00:14:13,987 --> 00:14:15,576
What about your chopsticks?

163
00:14:15,576 --> 00:14:18,209
- It's fine. I got a spare pair.
- Really?

164
00:14:18,209 --> 00:14:21,643
Oh, right.
There's something I wanted to mention.

165
00:14:21,643 --> 00:14:26,689
- What is it?
- We're taking over Hojo's project.

166
00:14:49,490 --> 00:14:53,370
So, with this, I want you to...

167
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:08,147
Don't tease your elders, rookie.

168
00:15:08,147 --> 00:15:09,167
Scary...

169
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:11,884
- I'm fine.
- Thanks, Nihei. I'll take care of Himari.

170
00:15:11,884 --> 00:15:13,697
Good work.

171
00:15:15,715 --> 00:15:19,928
Have I always been this jealous?

172
00:15:21,644 --> 00:15:23,621
Hello.

173
00:15:24,597 --> 00:15:26,119
Hey there.

174
00:15:26,119 --> 00:15:27,816
Taking a break too?

175
00:15:27,816 --> 00:15:32,278
Shibasaki was explaining the work
you're handing over to us,

176
00:15:32,278 --> 00:15:35,282
and we wanted some coffee.

177
00:15:35,282 --> 00:15:36,744
I see.

178
00:15:37,877 --> 00:15:40,177
A sudden business trip sounds rough.

179
00:15:40,177 --> 00:15:42,071
And to Fukuoka, no less.

180
00:15:43,505 --> 00:15:48,813
If it were just work and good food,
I'd go in a heartbeat.

181
00:15:49,765 --> 00:15:55,559
But I'm not great at inserting myself
into already established relationships.

182
00:15:55,559 --> 00:15:57,432
Really?

183
00:15:57,432 --> 00:16:01,153
But you're good at controlling people,
aren't you, Hojo?

184
00:16:04,570 --> 00:16:06,205
What do you mean?

185
00:16:07,352 --> 00:16:09,956
For the record, that's a compliment.

186
00:16:09,956 --> 00:16:14,733
You slip into people's hearts
and give them what they want to hear,

187
00:16:14,733 --> 00:16:17,364
to steer things your way.

188
00:16:17,364 --> 00:16:19,813
I could never pull that off.

189
00:16:20,526 --> 00:16:23,612
You make me sound like some kind of villain.

190
00:16:23,612 --> 00:16:25,848
That's not what I mean.

191
00:16:25,848 --> 00:16:27,448
But...

192
00:16:29,329 --> 00:16:33,182
You shouldn't do that to Shibasaki.

193
00:16:43,794 --> 00:16:45,875
Sorry to keep you waiting.

194
00:16:45,875 --> 00:16:48,565
You're on break too?

195
00:16:48,565 --> 00:16:51,145
Yeah, just taking a breather.

196
00:16:51,145 --> 00:16:52,907
I made one for you too.

197
00:16:52,907 --> 00:16:56,528
Thanks, Nihei. You're such a capable junior.

198
00:16:56,528 --> 00:16:58,614
Thank you.

199
00:16:58,614 --> 00:17:01,288
It's because I like you.

200
00:17:01,288 --> 00:17:02,501
Huh?

201
00:17:03,908 --> 00:17:05,423
You don't have to answer now.

202
00:17:05,423 --> 00:17:08,727
Anyway, let's get back to the handover.

203
00:17:08,727 --> 00:17:10,784
Wait, what?

204
00:17:10,784 --> 00:17:12,526
You're being loud.

205
00:17:23,195 --> 00:17:25,798
He deliberately stirred things up, huh?

206
00:17:39,167 --> 00:17:43,675
Now that you've met Yanami,
is anything on your mind?

207
00:17:45,644 --> 00:17:50,009
I'm just nervous about
whether I can fill your shoes.

208
00:17:50,009 --> 00:17:52,334
You'll be fine, Himari.

209
00:17:52,334 --> 00:17:54,316
Just call if you need me.

210
00:17:55,775 --> 00:17:59,858
You can even call to complain
in the middle of the night.

211
00:17:59,858 --> 00:18:02,922
Thanks, but I'll be okay.

212
00:18:02,922 --> 00:18:05,656
I can be reliable too, you know.

213
00:18:05,656 --> 00:18:07,287
I know you can.

214
00:18:07,287 --> 00:18:10,122
When in trouble, there's Lady Himari!

215
00:18:13,659 --> 00:18:16,586
So your business trip is in two days, huh?

216
00:18:17,408 --> 00:18:18,907
It's only two weeks.

217
00:18:18,907 --> 00:18:20,845
It'll fly by.

218
00:18:20,845 --> 00:18:23,598
Let's go on a date once everything's done.

219
00:18:23,598 --> 00:18:26,338
You're taking me
to Hamagasaki Beach, right?

220
00:18:26,338 --> 00:18:27,580
Right.

221
00:18:27,580 --> 00:18:31,992
Since it'll be after you come back,
that's in three weeks.

222
00:18:33,202 --> 00:18:34,593
I can't wait.

223
00:18:34,593 --> 00:18:37,753
Yeah. I'm looking forward to it.

224
00:18:41,915 --> 00:18:43,828
I'm hungry.

225
00:18:43,828 --> 00:18:47,336
Since it's late, let's grab food
instead of going back to work.

226
00:18:48,133 --> 00:18:51,906
Sorry, I've got things I need
to take care of back at the office.

227
00:18:53,001 --> 00:18:54,341
I see.

228
00:18:56,655 --> 00:18:59,953
Here. The key to my apartment.

229
00:18:59,953 --> 00:19:01,080
Huh?

230
00:19:01,730 --> 00:19:05,142
Grab some stuff from your place.

231
00:19:05,142 --> 00:19:07,739
Since you'll be visiting more often,

232
00:19:07,739 --> 00:19:09,888
make it so you can stay over whenever.

233
00:19:21,083 --> 00:19:22,615
Why do this all of a sudden?

234
00:19:23,362 --> 00:19:24,802
Is it too soon?

235
00:19:26,369 --> 00:19:27,943
No...

236
00:19:29,268 --> 00:19:31,510
I'm so happy.

237
00:19:36,582 --> 00:19:40,130
So, what did you tell him?

238
00:19:40,130 --> 00:19:41,751
Tell who?

239
00:19:41,751 --> 00:19:43,133
Nihei.

240
00:19:44,539 --> 00:19:47,425
That was just a joke.

241
00:19:47,425 --> 00:19:49,676
He's probably just messing with me.

242
00:19:51,277 --> 00:19:53,670
But what if he was serious?

243
00:19:53,670 --> 00:19:56,023
Then of course I'd turn him down.

244
00:19:56,023 --> 00:19:58,303
Because I have you, Kazumi.

245
00:20:01,767 --> 00:20:02,860
Yeah.

246
00:20:03,674 --> 00:20:06,252
I'll be going then.

247
00:20:06,930 --> 00:20:09,808
I'll come back as soon as I can.
Wait for me.

248
00:20:09,808 --> 00:20:12,023
Okay, see you.

249
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:29,708
<i>Nihei confessed to her
in front of me on purpose.</i>

250
00:20:31,681 --> 00:20:34,874
<i>Is it really okay
to leave Himari alone like this?</i>

251
00:20:44,667 --> 00:20:46,990
[Hojo]

252
00:20:47,899 --> 00:20:49,499
Coming!

253
00:20:51,442 --> 00:20:52,911
I'm home.

254
00:20:53,932 --> 00:20:55,818
Sorry for intruding.

255
00:20:55,818 --> 00:20:58,185
Just say "welcome back".

256
00:21:00,815 --> 00:21:02,458
Welcome back.

257
00:21:03,255 --> 00:21:04,855
Come in.

258
00:21:12,946 --> 00:21:14,648
Oh, nikujaga?

259
00:21:14,648 --> 00:21:18,105
Yeah, it's still cooking though.

260
00:21:18,105 --> 00:21:21,495
Thanks for waiting. Here you go.

261
00:21:21,495 --> 00:21:22,952
It's rolled dashi omelets.

262
00:21:22,952 --> 00:21:26,335
Yeah, you said you like it, right?

263
00:21:26,335 --> 00:21:28,647
<i>Himari never lies.</i>

264
00:21:28,647 --> 00:21:30,671
- Let's eat.
- Let's dig in.

265
00:21:31,850 --> 00:21:34,464
<i>The fact that she said she loves me,</i>

266
00:21:35,069 --> 00:21:38,163
<i>and that she'd turn down
Nihei's confession...</i>

267
00:21:39,994 --> 00:21:42,699
<i>I understand that objectively.</i>

268
00:21:44,034 --> 00:21:45,399
It's so good!

269
00:21:46,428 --> 00:21:49,464
Glad to hear that. Eat as much as you want.

270
00:21:49,464 --> 00:21:50,617
Try this too.

271
00:21:50,617 --> 00:21:51,864
Thanks.

272
00:21:55,646 --> 00:21:56,853
Himari.

273
00:22:02,777 --> 00:22:04,431
I love you, Kazumi.

274
00:22:04,431 --> 00:22:06,117
I love you too.

275
00:22:13,959 --> 00:22:18,011
<i>And yet, the unease won't go away.</i>

276
00:22:20,779 --> 00:22:22,488
<i>I know.</i>

277
00:22:23,875 --> 00:22:25,986
<i>This is fear.</i>

278
00:22:30,167 --> 00:22:31,712
Kazumi?

279
00:22:32,772 --> 00:22:35,100
That kinda hurts.

280
00:22:35,755 --> 00:22:37,202
Sorry.

281
00:22:38,211 --> 00:22:39,589
No, it's okay.

282
00:22:40,344 --> 00:22:41,618
What's wrong?

283
00:22:43,786 --> 00:22:45,366
Nothing.

284
00:22:46,877 --> 00:22:48,277
It's nothing.

285
00:22:53,001 --> 00:22:58,858
<i>Once again, the thought that
I may break something precious to me...</i>

286
00:23:00,773 --> 00:23:02,766
<i>makes me feel despair.</i>

287
00:23:45,221 --> 00:23:46,681
Here we go.

288
00:23:46,681 --> 00:23:48,110
Feels like a solid team.

289
00:23:48,110 --> 00:23:50,100
That's when I fell for you.

290
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:52,466
Am I not good enough?

291
00:23:52,466 --> 00:23:55,180
<i>Don't you trust me?</i>

292
00:23:55,180 --> 00:23:57,820
You don't need to change, Himari.

293
00:23:57,820 --> 00:23:59,820
<i>You won't answer me, huh?</i>

